# groups.cfg.example - security group membership template
#
# Copy to groups.cfg and replace YOUR_ADMIN_NAME with your login name:
#
#   cp groups.cfg.example groups.cfg
#
# Or from project root:
#   ./scripts/init-local-config.sh
#
# After editing, run: ./mud.sh restart
#
# Groups:
#   SECURE     - full admin (login.c master access)
#   ASSIST     - assistant admin
#   AMBASSADOR - ambassador tools

(SECURE) YOUR_ADMIN_NAME
(ASSIST) YOUR_ADMIN_NAME
(AMBASSADOR)
